This paper presents a dynamic executive for temporal plans with choice, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The use of dynamic plan execution strategies and autonomous agents suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The focus on labeled value set maintenance and weighted graph algorithms suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the use of prior work in Assumption-based Truth Maintenance Systems (ATMS) suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS).
